Four-month-old baby Evan Summerfield
A family have been left devastated after their four-month-old baby died from meningitis just 12 hours after laughing for the very first time
Evan Summerfield from Devon had just learned how to giggle and take his dummy out by himself but just hours later he was fighting for his life
His death has devastated his parents Shannon Summerfield
Meningitis Research Foundation estimates that there are around 3,400 cases of bacterial meningitis and septicaemia every year in the UK and Ireland
